00:13:21,834 --> 00:13:24,337
FUNCTIONAL PRODUCTS
WITH ENHANCEMENTS

00:13:24,337 --> 00:13:27,340
IS GROWING
IN THE MULTI‐BILLIONS.

00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:30,476
I WANT TO TAKE
MY EXISTING MINT AND GUM

00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:32,378
IN A WHOLE NEW DIRECTION,

00:13:32,378 --> 00:13:35,515
ADDING ENHANCEMENTS,
LIKE VITAMINS AND ANTIOXIDANTS.

00:13:35,515 --> 00:13:37,884
I'M ALSO INTRODUCING
MY CLIP'n'GO

00:13:37,884 --> 00:13:40,653
DUAL‐SIDED CONTACT LENS CASE.

00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:42,655
YOU FILL IT
WITH REWETTING SOLUTION

00:13:42,655 --> 00:13:44,991
AND AN EXTRA SET
OF CONTACT LENSES,

00:13:44,991 --> 00:13:49,195
AND IT CLIPS RIGHT ON
TO YOUR BACKPACK OR KEYCHAIN.

00:13:49,195 --> 00:13:52,699
MY PRODUCTS ARE WHAT YOU NEED
WHEN YOU NEED IT.

00:13:52,699 --> 00:13:56,002
AND WITH YOUR INVESTMENT TODAY
AND YOUR EXPERTISE,

00:13:56,002 --> 00:13:59,305
WE CAN TAKE THIS
TO A WHOLE NEW LEVEL.

00:13:59,305 --> 00:14:01,374
WHAT DOES
THE CONTACT LENS STUFF

00:14:01,374 --> 00:14:04,444
HAVE TO DO WITH THE GUM?

00:14:04,444 --> 00:14:06,879
WELL, THEY'RE
TWO SEPARATE PRODUCTS,

00:14:06,879 --> 00:14:09,248
BUT AT THE SAME TIME,
THEY'RE CLIP'n'GO.

00:14:09,248 --> 00:14:12,151
THEY'RE FOR PEOPLE ON THE GO.
ARE YOU REALLY IN
THE CONTAINER BUSINESS

00:14:12,151 --> 00:14:14,120
OR THE MINT BUSINESS
OR THE GUM BUSINESS

00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:16,823
OR ALL OF THE ABOVE?
(Robert)
OR THE CONTACT BUSINESS?

00:14:16,823 --> 00:14:19,826
ALL OF THE ABOVE.
WHAT ARE YOUR SALES
OF ALL THIS STUFF?

00:14:19,826 --> 00:14:22,628
WE HAD $817,000 OF SALE‐‐

00:14:22,628 --> 00:14:25,898
OF‐‐OF CASH LAST YEAR
IN SALES.
OH, WHOA.

00:14:25,898 --> 00:14:29,936
WE HAVE NOT INTRODUCED
THE LENZ YET AT ALL.

00:14:29,936 --> 00:14:32,672
WE WERE IN WALGREENS
AND WE WERE IN WINN‐DIXIE.

00:14:32,672 --> 00:14:35,775
AND‐‐AND RIGHT NOW
WE'RE ON AMAZON AND‐‐

00:14:35,775 --> 00:14:38,277
THE WORDS "WERE" AND "$800,000"

00:14:38,277 --> 00:14:40,313
DON'T REALLY
GO TOGETHER THAT WELL.

00:14:40,313 --> 00:14:42,382
WELL,
WE RAN OUT OF PRODUCT.

00:14:42,382 --> 00:14:45,551
HOW'S THAT POSSIBLE?
YOU GOT A SUCCESSFUL BUSINESS,

00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:48,121
YOU GOT $800,000 IN SALES,
AND YOU RUN OUT OF PRODUCT?

00:14:48,121 --> 00:14:50,923
IF YOU WORKED FOR ME,
I'D FIRE YOU RIGHT NOW.

00:14:50,923 --> 00:14:52,792
ONE OF THE THINGS ABOUT G‐‐

00:14:52,792 --> 00:14:54,794
ABOUT GOING AGAINST
THE BIG BRANDS

00:14:54,794 --> 00:14:57,263
IS THAT GETTING SHELF SPACE,
GETTING ON THERE‐‐

00:14:57,263 --> 00:15:00,366
IT'S VERY HARD
TO STAY ON THERE.
WHAT DID YOU MAKE ON $817,000?

00:15:00,366 --> 00:15:04,137
WELL, WE HAVEN'T MADE
REAL PROFIT YET.

00:15:04,137 --> 00:15:06,105
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

00:15:06,105 --> 00:15:08,708
WELL, WE PUT IT BACK
INTO THE BUSINESS.
(Robert)
YOU SAY YOU DON'T HAVE‐‐

00:15:08,708 --> 00:15:11,411
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY PEOPLE
HAVE COME OUT ONTO THIS CARPET

00:15:11,411 --> 00:15:13,846
THAT NEVER HAD ANYTHING NEAR
WHAT YOU HAD IN SALES?

00:15:13,846 --> 00:15:16,983
$800,000,
AND IT JUST VAPORIZED?

00:15:16,983 --> 00:15:20,086
OVERHEAD WAS RIDICULOUS.
WELL, THAT'S YOUR FAULT.

00:15:20,086 --> 00:15:23,156
I STILL DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT WENT WRONG.

00:15:23,156 --> 00:15:25,758
YOU SAY YOU DIDN'T HAVE SALES
'CAUSE YOU DIDN'T HAVE ORDER.

00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:28,661
IS IT BECAUSE YOU COULDN'T
FINANCE THE ORDERS

00:15:28,661 --> 00:15:31,130
OR IS IT BECAUSE
PEOPLE JUST STOPPED BUYING?
WELL, SOME OF THE‐‐

00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:33,132
SOME OF THE PLACES
THAT WE HAD THEM IN,

00:15:33,132 --> 00:15:36,068
SOME OF THE STORES, WERE DOING
IT FOR PROMOTIONAL PERIODS.

00:15:36,068 --> 00:15:38,337
IT WOULD RUN‐‐
BUT WHY DIDN'T THEY REORDER?

00:15:38,337 --> 00:15:40,339
THEY CHANGE ALL THE TIME.
I MEAN, ESPECIALLY

00:15:40,339 --> 00:15:42,575
IN THE CONFECTION
AND THE MINT AND GUM‐‐

00:15:42,575 --> 00:15:45,111
NOT THE MAINSTREAM BRANDS. YOU
CAN STILL FIND THE SAME GUM‐‐
OF COURSE YOU CAN.

00:15:45,111 --> 00:15:48,147
BOB, THAT'S HARD, BUT YOU'RE NOT
DOING A GOOD JOB OF EXPLAINING,

00:15:48,147 --> 00:15:52,485
'CAUSE SOMEWHERE,
YOU'RE LOSING ME.
(O'Leary) LET ME TRANSLATE,
'CAUSE I THINK I GOT IT.

00:15:52,485 --> 00:15:54,487
YOU HAVE A NOVELTY ITEM
THAT SELLS A COMMODITY‐‐

00:15:54,487 --> 00:15:55,988
MINTS AND GUMS.

00:15:55,988 --> 00:15:59,358
RETAILERS BROUGHT IT IN
BY THE HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS.

00:15:59,358 --> 00:16:01,360
THEY LOOK
AT THE MARGIN THEY MAKE

00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:03,729
AND HOW MUCH SHELF SPACE
YOUR PRODUCT TAKES UP,

00:16:03,729 --> 00:16:05,731
DIDN'T MEET THE HURDLE.

00:16:05,731 --> 00:16:07,900
THEY REPLACED YOUR STUFF
WITH OTHER STUFF THAT DOES.

00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:09,869
IF YOU CAN'T BEAT RUBBER BOOTS,
FOR EXAMPLE,

00:16:09,869 --> 00:16:11,370
YOU'RE NOT GONNA STAY IN.

00:16:11,370 --> 00:16:13,840
THEY WANT TO PUT
RUBBER BOOTS THERE INSTEAD.

00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,842
YOU HAD A SUGAR SPIKE.

00:16:15,842 --> 00:16:18,611
YOU WENT UP TO $800,000
AND STRAIGHT BACK DOWN

00:16:18,611 --> 00:16:20,913
BECAUSE YOU COULDN'T
STAY ON THE SHELF.

00:16:20,913 --> 00:16:22,815
TRUE OR FALSE?

00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:25,351
UM, WELL, THEY OR‐‐
THEY REORDERED AND REORDERED.

00:16:25,351 --> 00:16:28,421
AND THEN THEY...
STOPPED BECAUSE IT DIDN'T MEET

00:16:28,421 --> 00:16:30,723
THE GROSS MARGIN
PER LINEAR INCH.

00:16:30,723 --> 00:16:33,626
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS. RIGHT?
IS THAT CORRECT? YES‐‐JUST‐‐
IS THAT CORRECT, YES OR NO?

00:16:33,626 --> 00:16:35,761
YES. YES.
OKAY, ROB, ROB.

00:16:35,761 --> 00:16:38,731
MM‐HMM.
I'M OUT.

00:16:38,731 --> 00:16:41,434
WHAT DID YOU MAKE
ON $817,000?

00:16:41,434 --> 00:16:43,402
OUR MARGIN'S
ARE ABOUT 32%.

00:16:43,402 --> 00:16:47,406
SO ON $800,000 IN SALES,
YOU MADE ABOUT $240,000?

00:16:47,406 --> 00:16:50,610
RIGHT.
AND THEN YOU PAID
YOUR EXPENSES, YOURSELF.

00:16:50,610 --> 00:16:53,312
WHAT WAS LEFT
AT THE END OF THE DAY?

00:16:53,312 --> 00:16:55,648
WELL‐‐WELL, I HAD A, UH,
AN OPERATIONS MANAGER

00:16:55,648 --> 00:16:57,650
AND A PRESIDENT
WHO WAS REALLY DOING

00:16:57,650 --> 00:17:00,386
A LOT OF THE RUNNING
OF THE DAY‐TO‐DAY BUSINESS.

00:17:00,386 --> 00:17:02,922
DID YOU HAVE A LOT OF MONEY
YOU HAD TO THROW AT THIS,

00:17:02,922 --> 00:17:05,825
AND HOW MUCH DID YOU PUT IN?
COUPLE MILLION.

00:17:05,825 --> 00:17:08,427
(Robert) SORRY. YOU PUT WHAT?
A COUPLE MILLION.

00:17:08,427 --> 00:17:10,563
OF YOUR MONEY?
YEAH.

00:17:10,563 --> 00:17:13,699
WHERE'D YOU GET THAT MONEY FROM?
WHAT DO YOU DO FOR A LIVING?
I DID WHAT YOU DID.

00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:15,735
REAL ESTATE DEVELOPER.
GO BACK TO IT.

00:17:15,735 --> 00:17:18,337
SO, BOB, SERIOUSLY,
$2 MILLION?
YEAH.

00:17:18,337 --> 00:17:22,408
AND HOW MUCH OF IT
DO YOU HAVE LEFT?
MOST OF IT
WAS OVERHEAD.

00:17:22,408 --> 00:17:25,244
AS I SAID, WE MADE MISTAKES.
I MEAN, I GOTTA BE HONEST.

00:17:25,244 --> 00:17:28,147
THERE WERE MISTAKES.
OUR OVERHEAD WAS RIDICULOUS.
HOW MUCH WERE YOU PAYING
THESE OTHER GUYS IN OVERHEAD?

00:17:28,147 --> 00:17:30,182
$60,000 A MONTH.
OH.

00:17:30,182 --> 00:17:32,952
YEAH.
(Daymond) THIS IS GETTING
WORSE AND WORSE.

00:17:32,952 --> 00:17:35,388
I'M COMING TO WORK FOR YOU.
I WANT A JOB WITH YOU.

00:17:35,388 --> 00:17:37,390
BOB, HONEY, SWEETIE,
POOPSIE BABY,

00:17:37,390 --> 00:17:40,126
ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?

00:17:40,126 --> 00:17:42,528
HOW MUCH DID YOU GET
OUT OF THAT?

00:17:42,528 --> 00:17:44,897
WERE YOU ON A BIG SALARY,
ROLLING IN THE DOUGH?
NO, I DIDN'T GET ANYTHING.

00:17:44,897 --> 00:17:47,633
EVERY QUESTION,
IT GETS WORSE AND WORSE.
HOW MUCH IS LEFT, BOB?

00:17:47,633 --> 00:17:49,602
THERE ISN'T.
IT'S GONE?

00:17:49,602 --> 00:17:51,537
YEAH.

00:17:51,537 --> 00:17:54,373
(groans)
SO ARE YOU STILL FUNDING IT?
ARE YOU PUTTING MORE IN?

00:17:54,373 --> 00:17:57,977
NO, I HAVEN'T
FUNDED IT AT ALL.
HE'S COME HERE TO FUND IT
WITH YOUR MONEY.

00:17:57,977 --> 00:18:00,513
(laughs)
BOB, BA‐BASICALLY
WHAT I'VE LEARNED,

00:18:00,513 --> 00:18:02,048
THANKS TO BARBARA'S QUESTION,

00:18:02,048 --> 00:18:04,450
IS YOU TOOK $2 MILLION,

00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:06,752
HIRED SOME EXPENSIVE GUYS

00:18:06,752 --> 00:18:10,356
THAT GOT YOU
$800,000 IN SALES.

00:18:10,356 --> 00:18:14,327
THE SALES WENT AWAY.
YOU FIRED THOSE GUYS.

00:18:14,327 --> 00:18:16,996
$2 MILLION'S GONE.
YOU'RE DOWN TO ZERO.

00:18:16,996 --> 00:18:19,632
AND YOU'VE INVENTED
TWO NEW PRODUCT LINES,

00:18:19,632 --> 00:18:22,401
AND YOU WANT
TO START OVER AGAIN.

00:18:22,401 --> 00:18:24,337
ABSOLUTELY.

00:18:24,337 --> 00:18:27,607
I'M OUT AGAIN.
(sharks laugh)

00:18:27,607 --> 00:18:30,643
BOB, IT'S NOT AN INVESTMENT
THAT‐‐THAT I WOULD MAKE.

00:18:30,643 --> 00:18:32,712
I'M OUT ALSO.

00:18:32,712 --> 00:18:34,880
♪♪♪

00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:37,083
BOB, YOU'RE ALL OVER THE MAP,
MULTIPLE, UH,

00:18:37,083 --> 00:18:39,018
PRODUCT LINES
THAT AREN'T RELATED.

00:18:39,018 --> 00:18:41,988
THE ONE PRODUCT THAT WAS
SUCCESSFUL IS NOW AT ZERO.

00:18:41,988 --> 00:18:44,223
THEN YOU INVENTED OTHER STUFF.

00:18:44,223 --> 00:18:46,792
I MEAN, I'M TRYING TO
CHEW ON IT FROM EVERY ANGLE,

00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:49,228
AND IT‐‐
AND I STILL GET TO ZERO.

00:18:49,228 --> 00:18:51,130
I'M OUT.
OKAY.

00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:53,432
(O'Leary) BOB, I CAN'T DO IT.

00:18:53,432 --> 00:18:55,067
IT JUST MAKES NO SENSE.

00:18:55,067 --> 00:18:57,837
GO BACK TO REAL ESTATE.
I'M OUT.

00:19:02,074 --> 00:19:04,677
I THINK YOU HAD
A MIXED‐UP PRESENTATION.

00:19:04,677 --> 00:19:07,146
BUT I THINK
YOU'RE A DECENT SALESMAN.

00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:11,317
THERE'S AN OFFER COMING?
NO, THERE'S NO OFFER COMING.
I AM DEFINITELY OUT.

00:19:11,317 --> 00:19:13,552
I JUST WISH I HAD
SOMETHING NICE TO SAY TO YOU...

00:19:13,552 --> 00:19:15,888
BARB, I‐I BEG YOU,
PLEASE GIVE‐‐
BEFORE I SAY I'M OUT.

00:19:15,888 --> 00:19:18,824
PLEASE GIVE HIM $500,000.
NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:20,626
OKAY. GREAT, THANK YOU.
(Daymond) ALL RIGHT, THANK YOU.

00:19:20,626 --> 00:19:22,128
THANK YOU.
THANK YOU, BOB.

00:19:22,128 --> 00:19:23,629
(Barbara) THANK YOU.

00:19:23,629 --> 00:19:25,464
♪♪♪

00:19:25,464 --> 00:19:28,234
BOY, HE DID A BAD JOB
OF HOPPING AROUND ON THAT.

00:19:28,234 --> 00:19:31,303
'CAUSE HE HAD TO HIDE THINGS.
I THINK WE GOT TO THE BOTTOM
PRETTY QUICKLY.

00:19:31,303 --> 00:19:33,806
OH, WE GAVE HIM SURGERY.
WE GOT RIGHT TO IT.

00:19:33,806 --> 00:19:35,374
AMAZING STORY.

00:19:35,374 --> 00:19:38,377
I'D LIKE TO SAY TO THE SHARKS,
THANK YOU FOR HELPING ME

00:19:38,377 --> 00:19:40,546
SEE SOMETHING THAT
I REALLY NEEDED TO SEE,

00:19:40,546 --> 00:19:42,548
AND, UM...

00:19:42,548 --> 00:19:45,885
POTENTIALLY SAVE ME
SOME MORE LOSSES.

